climbs.name: Cecelia
climbs.fa: Bryce Johnson, found/cleaned by Nate Brun & co

content.description: Low roof climb starting on an obvious vertical flake/undercling and continuing up and left.
content.protection: Few pads, pretty low, climbs a bit of a ways out left.
content.location: Park at the large parking area which is actually the same parking as for A River Runs Through It. It will be on the left hand side if coming up canyon and you should be able to just barely see the dam from certain spots of the parking. Head up the opposite side of the road to the right of a massive wash. Head slightly down canyon, but uphill. A trail should emerge after no more than 1-2 minutes of walking; it will switch from heading more down canyon to heading more up the hillside. In around 5-10 minutes you'll arrive at the roof.
